Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Halve, deseed, and thinly slice @poblano pepper{1}(halved, deseeded, and thinly sliced into strips). Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered). Pick @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(picked) leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add onion and poblano; season with half the @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (You'll use the remaining Southwest Spice later.) Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{7-9%minutes}.

> TIP: If seasoning begins to burn before veggies are softened, add a splash of water.

Transfer to a #medium bowl{}; cover to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%ounce}; using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer. Cook, without stirring, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

Once turkey is browned on bottom, break up meat into pieces. Stir in @Tex-Mex paste{1}, remaining Southwest Spice, and @water{1/4%cup}. Bring to a simmer and cook until sauce has thickened and turkey is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Remove from heat; stir in 1 TBSP @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

> Use 2 TBSP butter for 4 servings.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pan{} over medium heat. Add @riced cauliflower{12%ounce}; season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and a pinch of @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until cauliflower is slightly softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Remove from heat. Stir in lime zest, half the cilantro, @butter{1%tbsp}, and a squeeze of lime juice.

> Use 1/2 tsp salt and 2 TBSP butter for 4 servings.

Divide cauliflower rice between #bowls{}. Top with turkey and veggies. Drizzle with @smoky red pepper crema{2%tbsp}. Garnish with remaining cilantro. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.